I always wonder how delivery drivers feel about going out in rain. I always feel bad ordering when it's raining.
Last year I bought some really good winter weather tires that will make the rain mostly meaningless.
I also default to wearing a hoodie in rainy weather, so my only concern is keeping the food hot and not soaked xD
I remember one time when I was younger, I had a pizza delivered, not knowing it was raining.
And then I forgot to tip him!
I felt so terrible I called the pizza place XD
I was just trying to get the guy out of the rain quickly and didn't think about it.

On the bright side, my other 6 reviews are 5-stars, and 1 customer thought I went above and beyond :ptv-hearts:
Order something through DoorDash, I need the monehs
